{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: bundle-eu-eps_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates the top-level FSH Bundle instance for a complete HL7 Europe
    Patient Summary (EPS) document. The Bundle aggregates every resource
    produced by the other EPS templates into a single self-contained FHIR
    document that can be validated, exchanged, and published as a formal
    FHIR example.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: BundleEuEps
    Fixed elements:
      type = #document

  USAGE: #example — NOT #inline
    Bundle templates are the only templates in the SYNDERAI project that use
    `Usage: #example`. All other templates use `Usage: #inline` (resources
    embedded inside a Bundle). The Bundle itself is the publishable artefact:
    it is the outermost container and is rendered by SUSHI as a standalone
    FHIR example file. Callers must not attempt to inline this instance.

  ROLE IN THE PIPELINE
    This template is always the LAST template invoked for an EPS document.
    All resources referenced in this Bundle must already have been generated
    by upstream template calls in the same pipeline run. The instance names
    referenced here (e.g. `Instance-Composition-{{ composition.instanceid }}`)
    must match the names registered via `setInstance()` in those upstream calls.

  FSH BUNDLE ENTRY REFERENCE PATTERN
    In FSH, a Bundle entry is expressed as two rules:
      * entry[slice].fullUrl  = "urn:uuid:<UUID>"
      * entry[slice].resource = <FSH-instance-name>
    The `.resource` value is a FSH instance name (e.g. `Instance-Patient-abc123`),
    NOT a UUID or URL. SUSHI resolves this reference to the compiled FHIR resource
    at build time. The `.fullUrl` provides the UUID that other resources use when
    referencing this entry via `Reference(urn:uuid:…)`.

    Single-entry slices (exactly one resource of that type):
      * entry[composition].fullUrl  = "urn:uuid:{{ composition.instanceid }}"
      * entry[composition].resource = Instance-Composition-{{ composition.instanceid }}
    Multi-entry slices (potentially multiple resources of the same type):
      * entry[practitionerrole][+].fullUrl  = "urn:uuid:{{ provider.instancerole }}"
      * entry[practitionerrole][=].resource = Instance-PractitionerRole-{{ provider.instancerole }}
    The [+]/[=] pair opens then addresses the same slice for fullUrl and resource.

  FIXED MANDATORY ENTRIES (always present, named slices)
    entry[composition]     — the EPS Composition (one per bundle, single slice)
    entry[patient]         — the Patient (one per bundle, single slice)
    entry[practitionerrole][+] — the author PractitionerRole (named + [+]/[=])
    entry[organization][+]     — the custodian Organisation  (named + [+]/[=])
    entry[practitioner][+]     — the individual Practitioner (named + [+]/[=])
    All five reference resources from provider-as-primarycarephysician-eps_fsh.twig.

  DYNAMIC SECTION ENTRIES (sections loop)
    The same `sections` associative dict used by composition-eu-eps_fsh.twig
    is iterated here to add each clinical resource to the Bundle:
      {% for slicename, section in sections %}
      {% for entry in section.entries %}
    Two fields from each entry object are used:
      entry.id       — UUID string for the .fullUrl rule
      entry.instance — complete FSH instance name string for the .resource rule
    The `entry.instance` field carries the full FSH instance name exactly as
    produced by setInstance() in the upstream clinical template
    (e.g. "Instance-Condition-abc123"). The template does NOT construct this
    name — it is pre-built by the PHP caller.
    The `bundleentryslicename` local variable is assembled and prepended to [+]
    in the same way as in the Composition templates.

  PROVENANCE TAIL — ALWAYS LAST
    Two unnamed entries close every EPS bundle:
      * entry[+].fullUrl  = "urn:uuid:{{ provenance.deviceid }}"
      * entry[=].resource = Instance-Device-{{ provenance.deviceid }}
      * entry[+].fullUrl  = "urn:uuid:{{ provenance.provenanceid }}"
      * entry[=].resource = Instance-Provenance-{{ provenance.provenanceid }}
    These reference the resources generated by device-and-provenance_fsh.twig.
    Unnamed [+] slices are used here (no named slice for provenance/device in
    the BundleEuEps profile). This identical tail appears in all three Bundle
    templates.

  NO HTML OUTPUT
    %%HEAD%% and %%HTML%% both use explicit `<!-- empty -->` HTML comment
    markers. No bag functions are called anywhere in this template.

  sectioncount
    Incremented once per section but never used in FSH output. Available as
    a debugging aid; produces no template output.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                             │ Type     │ Description                                  │
  ├──────────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ bundle.instanceid                    │ string   │ UUID for the Bundle resource.                │
  │ bundle.identifier                    │ string   │ Business identifier value for the bundle.    │
  │ composition.instanceid               │ string   │ UUID of the Composition resource.            │
  │ composition.date                     │ date     │ Document date; filtered to ISO 8601 UTC      │
  │                                      │          │ for the Bundle timestamp.                    │
  │ patient.instanceid                   │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.                │
  │ patient.name                         │ string   │ Full display name (for patientdisplay only). │
  │ patient.age                          │ string   │ Pre-computed age string (for Description).   │
  │ provider.instancerole                │ string   │ UUID of the author PractitionerRole.         │
  │ provider.instanceroleorg             │ string   │ UUID of the custodian Organisation.          │
  │ provider.instanceprovider            │ string   │ UUID of the individual Practitioner.         │
  │ sections                             │ dict     │ Same associative dict as the Composition     │
  │                                      │          │ template: slicename → section object.        │
  │   [slicename].entries                │ object[] │   Array of entry objects.                    │
  │     [n].id                           │ string   │     UUID for .fullUrl.                       │
  │     [n].instance                     │ string   │     Complete FSH instance name for .resource.│
  │     [n].bundleentryslicename         │ string?  │     Optional named entry slice.              │
  │ provenance.deviceid                  │ string   │ UUID of the Device resource.                 │
  │ provenance.provenanceid              │ string   │ UUID of the Provenance resource.             │
  └──────────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  GLOBAL VARIABLES USED
    HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID — OID root for the Bundle identifier system URI.

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-10-19
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Bundle-" ~ bundle.instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: BundleEuEps
Title: "HL7 Europe Patient Summary (EPS) Bundle"
{#
  patientdisplay set inline between FSH header lines.
  patient.age is a pre-computed display string supplied by the PHP caller.
  See composition-eu-eps_fsh.twig for full explanation of this pattern.
#}
{% set patientdisplay = patient.name ~ " (" ~ patient.age ~ " y/o) - synthetic data" %}
Description: "Complete HL7 Europe Patient Summary (EPS) FHIR Bundle example for {{ patientdisplay }}"
{#
  Usage: #example — ALL Bundle templates use #example, not #inline.
  The Bundle is the publishable outermost container rendered by SUSHI as a
  standalone FHIR example file. All other templates in the project use #inline.
#}
Usage: #example

* id = "{{ bundle.instanceid }}"

{# Bundle business identifier under the HL7 Europe OID namespace #}
* identifier.system = "urn:oid:{{ HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID }}"
* identifier.value = "{{ bundle.identifier }}"
* identifier.assigner.display = "HL7 Europe"

{# All document bundles carry type = #document #}
* type = #document

{#
  Bundle timestamp — ISO 8601 UTC datetime from the composition date.
  Same four-backslash escape pattern as in the Composition template.
#}
* timestamp = "{{ composition.date|date('Y-m-d\\TH:i:s\\Z') }}"

{#
  ── Fixed mandatory entries — single-slice (no [+]/[=]) ─────────────────────
  Exactly one Composition and one Patient per EPS document.
  .resource = FSH instance name (not UUID). SUSHI resolves this at build time.
#}
* entry[composition].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ composition.instanceid }}"
* entry[composition].resource = Instance-Composition-{{ composition.instanceid }}

* entry[patient].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}"
* entry[patient].resource = Instance-Patient-{{ patient.instanceid }}

{#
  ── Provider entries — named multi-slices ([+]/[=]) ─────────────────────────
  Named slices allow the profile to constrain which resource types may appear.
  [+] opens a new slice; [=] addresses the same slice for the .resource rule.
  All three reference resources from provider-as-primarycarephysician-eps_fsh.twig.
#}
* entry[practitionerrole][+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ provider.instancerole }}"
* entry[practitionerrole][=].resource = Instance-PractitionerRole-{{ provider.instancerole }}

* entry[organization][+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ provider.instanceroleorg }}"
* entry[organization][=].resource = Instance-Organization-{{ provider.instanceroleorg }}

* entry[practitioner][+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ provider.instanceprovider }}"
* entry[practitioner][=].resource = Instance-Practitioner-{{ provider.instanceprovider }}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  DYNAMIC SECTION ENTRIES — sections dict loop
  Iterates the same `sections` associative dict used by the Composition template.
  Each section's entries array provides:
    entry.id       — UUID for .fullUrl
    entry.instance — complete FSH instance name for .resource (pre-built by caller)
  bundleentryslicename is assembled identically to the Composition template.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% set sectioncount = 0 %} {# counter for debugging; produces no FSH output #}

{% for slicename, section in sections %}

{% set sectioncount = sectioncount + 1 %}

{% for entry in section.entries %}

{% if entry.bundleentryslicename is empty %}
{% set bundleentryslicename = "" %}
{% else %}
{% set bundleentryslicename = "[" ~ entry.bundleentryslicename ~ "]" %}
{% endif %}

* entry{{ bundleentryslicename }}[+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ entry.id }}"
* entry{{ bundleentryslicename }}[=].resource = {{ entry.instance }}

{% endfor %} {# entries #}

{% endfor %} {# sections #}

{#
  ── Provenance tail — always last, unnamed slices ────────────────────────────
  Device and Provenance instances from device-and-provenance_fsh.twig.
  Unnamed [+]/[=] used — the BundleEuEps profile has no named slices for these.
  This identical two-entry tail appears in all three Bundle templates.
#}
* entry[+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ provenance.deviceid }}"
* entry[=].resource = Instance-Device-{{ provenance.deviceid }}
* entry[+].fullUrl = "urn:uuid:{{ provenance.provenanceid }}"
* entry[=].resource = Instance-Provenance-{{ provenance.provenanceid }}

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
<!-- empty -->

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
<!-- empty -->
